
To compile and use it you have to do the binds shown in ./nix

This is the main nix source tree.
It's using 2M pages, and supports 1G pages.
In there, there are experimental frameworks for zero-copy, tubes, what else?

The main author was initially jmk and perhaps others from bell labs, when it was 9k.
Today it has been changed by many others including (|sort order):
esoriano
forsyth
jmk
nemo
npe
paurea
rminnich

You can reach as at nix A_T lsub.org
But don't write A_T like that.
